Third, financial economists are taking an increased interest in the characteristics of securities (e.g., Barclay and Smith1995a
            ,1995b
            ). As noted above, warrants represent an important source of financing for many firms, but warrants have received little attention in the finance literature. Our secondary purpose is to provide evidence on the characteristics of Australian warrants. We also explain some of their provisions in the context of the institutional setting in Australia.

We calculate the proportion of shares held by issuers (ALPHA) for each firm as follows: we use the offer price to compute the dollar value of the securities issued; we then express this value as a percent of the value of the firm (the dollar value of total shares and warrants, if any), again using the offer price; we refer to this ratio as %OUT. ALPHA is (
