               ).

A seasoned equity offering in Australia is either a rights offering or a private placement. We consider either of these events as additional equity financing and identify the first date after the IPO on which additional financing was received. Ninety‐six (52.2%) of the SIPO firms made an SEO within 3 years of their IPOs. Of the 90 PIPO firms, 53 (58.9%) made an SEO over the same interval. Although these proportions are consistent with the agency‐cost hypothesis, they are not significantly different at conventional levels (
